headline: Better Artificial Intelligence Stock: AT&T vs. Palantir Technologies
summary: AT&T is helping companies connect their AI devices and enabling edge computing artificial intelligence services.  Palantir's AI analytics services are tapping into a $1.7 trillion market.  Palantir is the better AI stock, but it comes at a hefty premium.

summary: Palantir Technologies Inc. (NASDAQ:PLTR) CEO Alex Karp has sold over $50 million in company shares this week, according to recent securities filings. headline: 3 High-Powered AI Stocks That Could Be the Next Palantir Technologies
summary: Palantir Technologies has taken the investing world by storm, thanks to its innovative use of artificial intelligence in the data analytics arena.  Palantir Technologies (NASDAQ: PLTR) has delivered extraordinary returns.  As a result, the artificial intelligence (AI) powerhouse's stock currently trades at a staggering 222 times forward earnings.

headline: Prediction: Palantir Stock Will Soar if Trump's One, Big, Beautiful Bill Passes Congress
summary: The GOP-backed bill includes $25 billion in funding for the Golden Dome missile defense system.  Palantir is one of a handful of companies that could be in a great position to win major contracts to build the system.  The stock could soar if the bill becomes law, but Palantir's valuation remains worrisome.

headline: Looking for the Next Palantir Stock? This New Artificial Intelligence (AI) Stock Is Up 150% in 2 Months
summary: CoreWeave stock has advanced 150% since the company held its initial public offering (IPO) in late March.  CoreWeave provides GPU-accelerated cloud infrastructure purpose-built for artificial intelligence workloads.  CoreWeave reported triple-digit sales growth in the first quarter, but interest payments on debt resulted in negative non-GAAP earnings.
